<org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription xmi:version="2.0" xmlns:xmi="http://www.omg.org/XMI" xmlns:org.eclipse.epf.uma="http://www.eclipse.org/epf/uma/1.0.6/uma.ecore" xmlns:rmc="http://www.ibm.com/rmc" rmc:version="7.5.1" xmlns:epf="http://www.eclipse.org/epf" epf:version="1.5.1" xmi:id="-GOkq21Zo_EBm9me2HazIuQ" name=",_cud-8KQUEeCUj4PP6f4uWQ" guid="-GOkq21Zo_EBm9me2HazIuQ" changeDate="2011-08-24T05:55:18.412-0700" version="7.5.1">
  <mainDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The specification of the verification, specifies and selects the simulation scenarios, test cases and test data based&#xD;
    upon the methods selected in the verification test plan.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    It is advised that the&amp;nbsp;user refers to ISO 26262 volume 8, clause 9.4.2 for further details on the contents of the&#xD;
    verification specification.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    There should not be any unspecified software components in the integration. If they exist, these should be identified&#xD;
    then either removed or deactivated.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    It is expected that the test environment shall correspond as far as possible to the target environment. If they are&#xD;
    differences between the test and target environment then further tests need to be defined (based upon the differences&#xD;
    between the source and object codes and the different environments) to provide proper coverage of the&amp;nbsp;integration&#xD;
    tests&amp;nbsp;on the target environment for subsequent phases. Example of this can be due to the different bit&#xD;
    widths&amp;nbsp;of data words and address words of the processors involved.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    If it is not possible to carry out the software integration tests on the target processor , a process emulator can be&#xD;
    used, else the software integration testing is executed on the development system.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Other environments in which the software integration tests can be carried out&amp;nbsp;are&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;blockquote>&#xD;
    &lt;blockquote style=&quot;MARGIN-RIGHT: 0px&quot; dir=&quot;ltr&quot;>&#xD;
        &lt;p>&#xD;
            Model in the loop tests&#xD;
        &lt;/p>&#xD;
        &lt;p>&#xD;
            Software in the loop tests&#xD;
        &lt;/p>&#xD;
        &lt;p>&#xD;
            Processor in the loop tests&#xD;
        &lt;/p>&#xD;
        &lt;p>&#xD;
            Hardware in the loop tests&#xD;
        &lt;/p>&#xD;
    &lt;/blockquote>&lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
    &lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;/blockquote></mainDescription>
  <purpose>To specify the test methods and test cases that are used to test the SW units that are integrated together at a particular&#xD;
level of the items SW hierarchy.</purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
